    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-23T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="587"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/404: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-23T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 23, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. I have submitted to the Minister for Foreign Affairs the text of press
                    release which accompanied Department’s instruction No. 126, June 15 which is
                    satisfactory to him. Dr. Tobar informs me however that there is some probability
                    the 30% plan referred to in previous correspondence will go into effect July 1.
                    He has supplied me with a draft of the latter and thinks it would be well for
                    the Department to understand its terms, after which he will be agreeable to
                    publication of whatever release the Department deems to be convenient. Copy will
                    be forwarded by air mail leaving here tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
